      "title": "Core Concepts of Thai Cuisine",
      "content": "Thai cuisine is celebrated for its balance of flavors, including sweet, sour, salty, and spicy. Understanding these core concepts is essential for any beginner.",
      "layout": "standard"
    },
    {
      "title": "Flavor Profiles",
      "content": "Explore the four main flavor profiles in Thai cooking:\n- Sweet: Derived from palm sugar or fruits.\n- Sour: Commonly from lime juice or tamarind.\n- Salty: Typically from fish sauce or soy sauce.\n- Spicy: Often from fresh or dried chilies.",
      "layout": "standard"
    },
    {
      "title": "Essential Ingredients",
      "content": "Familiarize yourself with essential Thai ingredients:\n- Fish sauce: A key source of saltiness.\n- Palm sugar: Adds sweetness.\n- Fresh herbs: Like cilantro and basil for freshness.\n- Chilies: For that spicy kick.",
      "layout": "standard"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cooking Techniques",
      "content": "Learn about common cooking techniques in Thai cuisine:\n- Stir-frying: Quick and flavorful.\n- Steaming: Preserves nutrients and flavors.\n- Grilling: Adds a smoky taste.\n- Currying: Blending spices and ingredients.",
      "layout": "standard"
    }
  ]
}
